I regret that.

609
01:07:15,344 --> 01:07:16,846
Know this:

610
01:07:17,471 --> 01:07:20,850
Every time I see your face,
I wanna rip your throat out.

611
01:07:28,232 --> 01:07:29,525
Fine.

612
01:07:31,986 --> 01:07:34,113
You win the pissing contest.

613
01:07:46,500 --> 01:07:47,710
What do I do?

614
01:07:47,919 --> 01:07:49,170
Nothing.

615
01:07:49,378 --> 01:07:52,882
He's making a mistake.
He thinks he has time. He doesn't.

616
01:07:53,090 --> 01:07:55,885
Seth Frank's too good.
He'll bring him in.

617
01:07:56,636 --> 01:07:57,803
Then what?

618
01:07:59,430 --> 01:08:00,556
Then I kill him.

619
01:08:08,314 --> 01:08:09,607
Miss Whitney?

620
01:08:09,857 --> 01:08:11,234
Thanks.

621
01:08:21,244 --> 01:08:22,370
Miss Whitney?

622
01:08:23,579 --> 01:08:25,957
I'm Seth Frank. Excuse me.

623
01:08:33,172 --> 01:08:34,382
Thanks.

624
01:08:38,344 --> 01:08:41,889
For a tough prosecutor, you sure
don't resemble your reputation.

625
01:08:43,182 --> 01:08:44,517
Is that good or bad?

626
01:08:48,813 --> 01:08:49,814
I don't know.

627
01:08:52,358 --> 01:08:55,027
Look, lieutenant,
I told you on the phone.

628
01:08:55,444 --> 01:08:59,699
I'm not involved with my father.
So this is a waste of time.

629
01:09:00,533 --> 01:09:03,160
Do you expect me to walk out of here?

630
01:09:05,621 --> 01:09:06,706
All right.

631
01:09:09,000 --> 01:09:10,251
All right.

632
01:09:11,085 --> 01:09:12,962
Your father disappeared.

633
01:09:16,173 --> 01:09:18,217
-I need your help.
-Look.

634
01:09:18,467 --> 01:09:20,720
Lieutenant, I don't know the man.

635
01:09:20,970 --> 01:09:25,099
He was in jail. When he got out,
my mom and I lived by ourselves.

636
01:09:25,349 --> 01:09:27,602
He doesn't care about me.

637
01:09:27,852 --> 01:09:29,854
I've seen him once this past year.

638
01:09:30,104 --> 01:09:31,522
Yeah, when?

639
01:09:32,857 --> 01:09:33,774
A few days ago.

640
01:09:35,568 --> 01:09:39,280
He said he might leave town.
I helped you. Can I work now?

641
01:09:40,448 --> 01:09:43,117
-Any idea where he went?
-Quit wasting my time.

642
01:09:43,367 --> 01:09:45,494
He doesn't want you to find him,
you won't.

643
01:09:45,745 --> 01:09:47,997
You're saying
he skipped the country?

644
01:09:48,206 --> 01:09:50,625
I'm saying you won't recognize him.

645
01:09:51,584 --> 01:09:53,544
He could be right around the corner.

646
01:09:55,463 --> 01:09:57,381
-He always had a safe house.
-Where?

647
01:09:57,590 --> 01:09:58,424
He never said.

648
01:09:58,674 --> 01:10:00,301
How do you know he had one?

649
01:10:02,053 --> 01:10:03,888
My mother loved him, all right?

650
01:10:04,096 --> 01:10:08,476
Even after she left him, when she was
dying, he was all she talked about.

651
01:10:09,518 --> 01:10:11,771
"lf only he hadn't done this.

652
01:10:12,021 --> 01:10:14,690
-If only he hadn't done that. "
-What else?

653
01:10:19,612 --> 01:10:21,906
-How long has he lived here?
-Years.

654
01:10:22,156 --> 01:10:23,449
Never been.

655
01:10:27,912 --> 01:10:30,998
This is a strange place
for a thief to leave a key.

656
01:10:31,249 --> 01:10:33,251
He always did that.

657
01:11:49,744 --> 01:11:54,165
He left in a hurry. I wonder what
scares a professional thief like that.

658
01:12:05,885 --> 01:12:08,137
He wasn't at these places.

659
01:12:09,931 --> 01:12:12,516
My college graduation. . .

660
01:12:14,018 --> 01:12:17,688
. . .my law school graduation,
the night my mother and l. . .

661
01:12:17,897 --> 01:12:22,109
. . .we went out to celebrate
because I'd gotten my first job.

662
01:12:22,944 --> 01:12:25,488
Me alone on the steps.
I'd won my first case.

663
01:12:29,367 --> 01:12:31,369
I used to think sometimes. . . .

664
01:12:35,748 --> 01:12:40,044
Sometimes I'd come home and could sense
that he'd been in the apartment.

665
01:12:40,419 --> 01:12:45,550
That he'd checked the fridge, shook
his head because I never ate right.

666
01:12:46,801 --> 01:12:50,680
I mean, I know it sounds crazy,
but I've always. . . .

667
01:12:51,264 --> 01:12:53,599
I've always felt
that he was around.

668
01:12:54,183 --> 01:12:56,644
You can do a good thing.
Help me bring him in.

669
01:12:56,894 --> 01:12:59,021
Leave a message
you're worried about him.

670
01:12:59,522 --> 01:13:00,523
No.

671
01:13:00,731 --> 01:13:03,651
It's true. You're worried.
This is no normal case.

672
01:13:03,901 --> 01:13:06,988
His life is in danger.
You call, you could save him.

673
01:13:07,613 --> 01:13:08,865
He won't come.

674
01:13:09,073 --> 01:13:11,534
Of course he'll come.
You're all he has.

675
01:13:11,993 --> 01:13:15,371
He's on the run and he's scared
because he'll get caught.

676
01:13:15,788 --> 01:13:18,332
-You don't know the heat.
-He's not a murderer.

677
01:13:19,083 --> 01:13:20,877
Maybe he is innocent.

678
01:13:21,419 --> 01:13:24,255
If that's true, I'll have him
home in a few hours.

679
01:13:26,215 --> 01:13:29,844
What if a hotshot trying to
make a reputation tracks him down?

680
01:13:32,471 --> 01:13:34,807
I can guarantee his safety.

681
01:13:35,057 --> 01:13:37,560
You make the call,
I'll make a promise.

682
01:13:38,102 --> 01:13:39,604
You'll have him back.

683
01:13:58,039 --> 01:14:00,541
-Seth Frank.
-Hi.

684
01:14:01,542 --> 01:14:03,669
I left a message on his machine.

685
01:14:03,920 --> 01:14:08,090
He called me back within the hour
and I'm meeting him tomorrow.

686
01:14:08,758 --> 01:14:09,884
Where?

687
01:14:11,469 --> 01:14:14,055
Open-air place near my office,
Cafe Alonzo.

688
01:14:14,847 --> 01:14:15,806
What time?

689
01:14:16,641 --> 01:14:18,059
Four o 'clock.

690
01:14:19,185 --> 01:14:20,978
It'll be deserted then.

691
01:14:22,522 --> 01:14:24,315
Sounds good. Thanks a lot.

692
01:14:24,524 --> 01:14:26,400
-Bye.
-Bye-bye.

693
01:15:16,117 --> 01:15:17,451
Dad, hi.

