You can call anytime.

769
01:26:17,695 --> 01:26:19,572
Want me to get
someone to stay here?

770
01:26:20,907 --> 01:26:23,409
No, I wanna get some sleep.

771
01:26:23,659 --> 01:26:25,912
Surveillance is outside
until it's over.

772
01:26:26,162 --> 01:26:28,539
I've got a feeling he'll contact you.

773
01:26:29,707 --> 01:26:31,626
You're on a hot streak, I guess.

774
01:26:33,044 --> 01:26:34,837
Listen, I'm sorry.

775
01:26:39,008 --> 01:26:41,052
Anything unusual at all. . .

776
01:26:41,510 --> 01:26:43,179
. . .call right away.

777
01:26:43,429 --> 01:26:44,931
It's not a bother.

778
01:26:47,016 --> 01:26:48,309
I live alone.

779
01:26:50,311 --> 01:26:51,938
You said.

780
01:26:53,356 --> 01:26:54,857
Feeble.

781
01:26:58,402 --> 01:27:00,571
You want something for the road?

782
01:27:02,532 --> 01:27:04,242
I got water and water.

783
01:27:06,577 --> 01:27:07,453
Deal.

784
01:27:23,094 --> 01:27:25,096
A Pellegrino would be great.

785
01:27:27,223 --> 01:27:29,475
What's so funny?
I say it wrong?

786
01:27:31,018 --> 01:27:32,812
I'm tired.

787
01:27:33,688 --> 01:27:35,314
I'm just tired.

788
01:27:46,033 --> 01:27:47,618
Listen. . .

789
01:27:47,827 --> 01:27:49,495
. . .there's one thing. . .

790
01:27:50,371 --> 01:27:52,206
. . .I forgot to tell you.

791
01:27:54,333 --> 01:27:55,960
I live alone.

792
01:28:01,215 --> 01:28:02,675
Lock up behind me.

793
01:28:08,347 --> 01:28:09,932
-How's that?
-Real good.

794
01:28:10,141 --> 01:28:12,018
Now get some sleep.

795
01:28:12,727 --> 01:28:14,312
Thank you.

796
01:28:21,986 --> 01:28:24,947
I betrayed you twice, Luther.
You should know that.

797
01:28:25,239 --> 01:28:27,033
You're not the first.

798
01:28:34,290 --> 01:28:35,583
Why'd you come?

799
01:28:36,459 --> 01:28:39,086
I can't have my daughter
thinking I was a murderer.

800
01:28:42,048 --> 01:28:45,384
No, I mean this afternoon.
Why'd you come?

801
01:28:45,635 --> 01:28:48,429
You suspected something
or you wouldn't have prepared.

802
01:28:48,679 --> 01:28:50,806
My daughter wanted to see me.

803
01:28:56,812 --> 01:28:59,982
The robbery was going fine
until they came in.

804
01:29:00,441 --> 01:29:01,692
They were drunk.

805
01:29:01,943 --> 01:29:04,153
I was hidden in the vault.

806
01:29:04,362 --> 01:29:06,697
And the sex had started
getting rough. . .

807
01:29:06,906 --> 01:29:08,950
. . .and he started beating her. . .

808
01:29:09,242 --> 01:29:12,119
. . .started strangling her.
I thought he'd kill her.

809
01:29:12,370 --> 01:29:16,249
Then she somehow got the upper hand.

810
01:29:16,707 --> 01:29:20,711
She was gonna stab him with
a letter opener and two guys shot her.

811
01:29:21,712 --> 01:29:24,215
The same two guys
who tried for you today.

812
01:29:25,841 --> 01:29:27,093
Possibly.

813
01:29:27,343 --> 01:29:29,679
Unless Walter Sullivan
was taking a shot.

814
01:29:32,014 --> 01:29:34,016
It's a pretty powerful enemy.

815
01:29:34,267 --> 01:29:36,060
That's very good going.

816
01:29:37,770 --> 01:29:40,731
Not as powerful as
the President of the United States.

817
01:29:42,900 --> 01:29:44,026
That's right.

818
01:29:44,277 --> 01:29:46,612
Alan Richmond, he was the drunk.

819
01:29:47,488 --> 01:29:49,407
The two guys were Secret Service.

820
01:29:49,657 --> 01:29:52,368
Chief of Staff Russell
handled the cover-up.

821
01:29:53,327 --> 01:29:55,872
Well, then you go to the police.

822
01:29:56,163 --> 01:29:59,208
That's what innocent people do.
They go to the police.

823
01:29:59,417 --> 01:30:00,877
Sure.

824
01:30:01,085 --> 01:30:02,795
That young man who was here. . .

825
01:30:03,045 --> 01:30:05,673
. . .he'd believe me
over the President, right?

826
01:30:07,091 --> 01:30:08,676
Why should I believe you?

827
01:30:10,469 --> 01:30:12,555
Because I swear to you, Kate.

828
01:30:13,014 --> 01:30:14,974
I swear to you on Mattie's grave.

829
01:30:16,309 --> 01:30:17,351
That's right.

830
01:30:17,810 --> 01:30:21,731
Your mother's grave. I'd kill myself
before I'd lie about that.

831
01:30:23,566 --> 01:30:25,276
Oh, Jesus, Luther.

832
01:30:25,526 --> 01:30:27,570
-Yeah. I know.
-They'll kill you.

833
01:30:30,072 --> 01:30:32,783
-I know.
-Can you run?

834
01:30:34,535 --> 01:30:38,206
I was all set to.
I was at the airport ready to go.

835
01:30:39,040 --> 01:30:41,125
Then there was that press conference.

836
01:30:42,126 --> 01:30:45,713
And there was Richmond
using old man Sullivan.

837
01:30:47,757 --> 01:30:50,301
You know, I might not
have been able to. . .

838
01:30:50,551 --> 01:30:53,012
. . .save Christy Sullivan. . .

839
01:30:53,930 --> 01:30:55,598
. . .but I didn't even try.

840
01:30:57,266 --> 01:30:58,851
What are you gonna do?

841
01:31:02,271 --> 01:31:04,315
I'll think of something.

842
01:31:13,407 --> 01:31:16,202
I watched you argue a case last year.

843
01:31:16,410 --> 01:31:17,453
You won it.

844
01:31:18,746 --> 01:31:21,249
Thank God you got
your mother's brains.

845
01:31:22,667 --> 01:31:23,876
Dangerous outside.

846
01:31:26,420 --> 01:31:28,214
It always is.

847
01:31:50,194 --> 01:31:51,821
Excuse me.

848
01:31:52,238 --> 01:31:54,407
Could you give this
to Gloria Russell?

849
01:31:54,657 --> 01:31:58,494
-Anything for me to sign?
-No, you have an honest face.

850
01:32:37,742 --> 01:32:39,577
Oh, my God.

851
01:33:01,766 --> 01:33:03,392
You're a vision tonight.

852
01:33:03,851 --> 01:33:06,896
Thank you, Mr. President.

853
01:33:07,396 --> 01:33:09,899
And thank you, Mr. President.

854
01:33:10,107 --> 01:33:12,527
For. . .?
Come again.

855
01:33:18,282 --> 01:33:19,116
You know.

856
01:33:23,454 --> 01:33:26,290
You sent it to me this afternoon.

857
01:33:27,625 --> 01:33:29,001
Of course.

858
01:33:31,379 --> 01:33:34,048
Would you excuse me, all?

859
01:33:34,298 --> 01:33:37,969
I'm overcome with a desire
to dance with my chief of staff.

860
01:33:38,636 --> 01:33:40,888
Look after this for me, would you?

861
01:34:03,160 --> 01:34:05,079
What is this nonsense?

862
01:34:05,371 --> 01:34:07,373
I'm hoping there's an explanation.

863
01:34:08,040 --> 01:34:10,626
Your gift, Alan. I was. . .

864
01:34:10,877 --> 01:34:12,378
. . .overwhelmed.

865
01:34:12,628 --> 01:34:16,132
And, you know, your note
was so gratifying.

866
01:34:21,429 --> 01:34:22,680
I sent a note?

867
01:34:23,514 --> 01:34:25,349
Yes, yes.

868
01:34:25,600 --> 01:34:27,894
You think I don't know your writing?

869
01:34:28,144 --> 01:34:30,980
I assumed you wanted me
to wear it tonight.

870
01:34:31,397 --> 01:34:34,066
-Gloria, it's lovely.
-Yes.

871
01:34:34,275 --> 01:34:35,943
And you know what else?

872
01:34:37,195 --> 01:34:38,446
What, Alan?

873
01:34:40,823 --> 01:34:43,367
Christy wore it the night
she was killed.

874
01:34:51,209 --> 01:34:52,460
Know what this means?

875
01:34:52,668 --> 01:34:53,920
No.

876
01:34:54,170 --> 01:34:55,963
Whitney's been heard from.

877
01:35:03,554 --> 01:35:06,140
It's not precisely the first time.

878
01:35:09,977 --> 01:35:12,063
You been keeping things from me?

879
01:35:14,065 --> 01:35:17,902
Well, it's just that you have
so much on your plate.

880
01:35:18,152 --> 01:35:20,196
We wanted to spare you.

881
01:35:24,575 --> 01:35:27,161
He sent me a Polaroid. . .

882
01:35:27,411 --> 01:35:29,747
. . .of the letter opener yesterday.

883
01:35:45,805 --> 01:35:47,890
I have to give this some thought.

884
01:35:52,019 --> 01:35:54,146
Come to my office in the morning.

885
01:35:55,273 --> 01:35:58,317
This'll make an interesting
chapter in my memoirs.

886
01:36:12,498 --> 01:36:14,709
Do we know who the forger is?

887
01:36:14,959 --> 01:36:19,171
I talked to Seth Frank. Apparently,
Whitney learned how in prison.

888
01:36:22,800 --> 01:36:24,385
A gifted man.

889
01:36:26,137 --> 01:36:27,638
How close are we to him?

890
01:36:28,389 --> 01:36:30,391
We're working around the clock.

891
01:36:32,310 --> 01:36:34,187
Well, that's good to know.

892
01:36:35,354 --> 01:36:36,689
He'll make a mistake.

893
01:36:37,481 --> 01:36:39,400
Well, that's good to know too.

894
01:36:47,283 --> 01:36:48,534
There is. . .

895
01:36:48,743 --> 01:36:50,661
. . .one other thing. . .

896
01:36:51,454 --> 01:36:53,372
. . .that we need to take care of.

897
01:36:55,958 --> 01:36:57,960
He has a daughter, doesn't he?

898
01:36:59,879 --> 01:37:01,464
You sure you wanna do that?

899
01:37:04,175 --> 01:37:05,426
Sir?

900
01:37:10,306 --> 01:37:14,310
She's a young prosecutor.
Prosecutors ask questions.

901
01:37:16,604 --> 01:37:18,773
Maybe she knows what he knows.

902
01:37:23,903 --> 01:37:25,488
Let's get cracking, boys.

903
01:37:29,534 --> 01:37:31,661
Show that you love your country.

904
01:37:56,477 --> 01:37:57,937
How's Kate doing?

905
01:37:58,354 --> 01:37:59,438
Where are you?

906
01:37:59,647 --> 01:38:02,358
I won't hang around for you
to trace the call.

907
01:38:02,567 --> 01:38:03,985
Just answer the question.

908
01:38:04,360 --> 01:38:06,487
She couldn't be in better hands.

909
01:38:06,696 --> 01:38:10,032
Secret Service is
taking over surveillance.

910
01:38:13,578 --> 01:38:14,829
Hello?

911
01:38:18,457 --> 01:38:19,834
Hello?

912
01:41:30,483 --> 01:41:32,318
It's entered in the chart.

913
01:41:33,236 --> 01:41:36,489
We upped her from
250 to 500 milligrams.

914
01:42:17,947 --> 01:42:20,283
Nurse, I need you right away, please.

915
01:42:20,867 --> 01:42:22,368
He's having a seizure.

916
01:43:27,475 --> 01:43:30,144
Dr. Kevorkian, I presume.

917
01:43:31,270 --> 01:43:35,149
My guess is that this is right
in your carotid artery about now.

918
01:43:36,067 --> 01:43:38,319
You're gonna get a little woozy.

919
01:43:38,778 --> 01:43:40,613
But if I give you the rest. . .

920
01:43:40,863 --> 01:43:44,116
. . .it'll fry your brain down
to the size of a peanut.

921
01:43:44,534 --> 01:43:45,785
Drop that.

922
01:44:00,883 --> 01:44:02,260
Luther. . .

923
01:44:03,302 --> 01:44:04,637
. . .he was my President.

924
01:44:05,555 --> 01:44:07,265
Right or wrong.

925
01:44:08,391 --> 01:44:10,226
Well, he made a mistake.

926
01:44:10,434 --> 01:44:11,811
You made a mistake.

927
01:44:14,564 --> 01:44:18,109
When you went after my girl,
that was entirely unacceptable.

928
01:44:20,820 --> 01:44:21,904
Mercy.

929
01:44:25,074 --> 01:44:26,492
I'm fresh out.

930
01:44:36,961 --> 01:44:38,045
Daddy?

931
01:44:41,883 --> 01:44:43,426
Go to sleep, darling.

932
01:45:15,416 --> 01:45:17,126
Oh, Jesus!

933
01:45:19,295 --> 01:45:20,796
Just one question.

934
01:45:21,047 --> 01:45:25,009
Did Walter Sullivan say
why Christy didn't go to Barbados?

935
01:45:26,052 --> 01:45:28,179
Just that she changed her mind.

936
01:45:29,096 --> 01:45:31,057
You know who did it, don't you?

937
01:45:32,934 --> 01:45:35,895
So will you.
Check your phones.

938
01:45:41,943 --> 01:45:43,611
Good night, Mr. Sullivan.

939
01:46:04,632 --> 01:46:06,717
You're taking a shortcut, Tommy?

940
01:46:10,096 --> 01:46:12,807
I'm your substitute driver tonight.

941
01:46:14,350 --> 01:46:16,519
Don't worry about Tommy.
He's fine.

942
01:46:17,228 --> 01:46:19,063
Very unusual.

943
01:46:19,856 --> 01:46:21,566
What do I call you?

944
01:46:22,483 --> 01:46:24,068
Luther, sir.

945
01:46:25,570 --> 01:46:29,198
And are you familiar with
how to get to my townhouse, Luther?

946
01:46:29,448 --> 01:46:31,158
Oh, yes, sir.

947
01:46:31,367 --> 01:46:33,411
I know where all your houses are.

948
01:46:33,619 --> 01:46:35,746
I'm the man who robbed you.

949
01:46:39,166 --> 01:46:41,502
You're the man who tried to kill me.

950
01:46:43,462 --> 01:46:45,756
I'm sorry I missed.

951
01:46:47,174 --> 01:46:49,927
I believe in the Old Testament, sir.

952
01:46:50,428 --> 01:46:52,889
There's nothing wrong with
an eye for an eye. . .

953
01:46:53,139 --> 01:46:54,849
. . .when a terrible deed is done.

954
01:46:55,683 --> 01:46:57,852
A deed such as yours.

955
01:46:58,728 --> 01:47:00,563
You'd like to believe that.

956
01:47:00,771 --> 01:47:03,274
That'd be simple for you
to believe that.

957
01:47:03,482 --> 01:47:05,776
What do I have to gain by being here?

958
01:47:06,611 --> 01:47:08,112
I have no idea.

959
01:47:08,362 --> 01:47:09,989
You going to rob me again?

960
01:47:10,364 --> 01:47:12,700
I don't need your money, Mr. Sullivan.

961
01:47:12,950 --> 01:47:15,369
Did you check your vault lately?

962
01:47:16,037 --> 01:47:18,080
I put everything back.

963
01:47:19,624 --> 01:47:23,085
I'm afraid we're a little late
for an attempt at leniency.

964
01:47:27,340 --> 01:47:29,759
A lot of crap's coming
down tonight, sir.

965
01:47:29,967 --> 01:47:31,677
You wanna be a player or not?

966
01:47:31,928 --> 01:47:34,472
You wanna know what happened
or don't you?

967
01:47:34,680 --> 01:47:36,432
Because I was there.

968
01:47:37,058 --> 01:47:38,476
I want to know.

969
01:47:39,101 --> 01:47:41,479
You think you can stand
hearing about it?

970
01:47:41,729 --> 01:47:44,065
How he beat her,
tried to strangle her?

971
01:47:44,315 --> 01:47:46,025
You really wanna know?

972
01:47:47,276 --> 01:47:49,820
I could walk through fire.

973
01:47:51,405 --> 01:47:53,533
I was in the vault when they came in.

974
01:47:53,741 --> 01:47:55,409
They were drunk.

975
01:47:55,618 --> 01:47:57,036
He knocked her around.

976
01:47:57,245 --> 01:47:59,163
She fought back.

977
01:47:59,872 --> 01:48:01,249
He got really rough.

978
01:48:01,499 --> 01:48:03,543
She tried to defend herself.

979
01:48:03,751 --> 01:48:05,628
Well, he started screaming. . .

980
01:48:05,836 --> 01:48:08,506
. . .sniveling simp he is.

981
01:48:08,714 --> 01:48:10,341
Who else was in my house?

982
01:48:10,550 --> 01:48:13,261
Secret Service.
They're the ones who shot her.

983
01:48:14,053 --> 01:48:15,096
Nonsense.

984
01:48:15,888 --> 01:48:18,057
Gloria Russell handled the cover-up.

985
01:48:18,266 --> 01:48:19,350
Stop this!

986
01:48:19,809 --> 01:48:21,435
You wanna know who it was?

987
01:48:21,644 --> 01:48:22,812
It was you.

988
01:48:23,312 --> 01:48:27,066
Come on, Mr. Sullivan.
We're too old to bullshit each other.

989
01:48:27,692 --> 01:48:28,901
Who was it, then?

990
01:48:29,110 --> 01:48:30,611
You know.

991
01:48:33,364 --> 01:48:34,782
Don't shake your head.

992
01:48:38,661 --> 01:48:41,956
When you're alone and rage takes over
and you want revenge. . .

993
01:48:42,206 --> 01:48:44,625
. . .what face do you put
with your enemy?

994
01:48:58,556 --> 01:48:59,932
Stop the car!

995
01:49:00,141 --> 01:49:01,809
We're going straight ahead.

996
01:49:04,061 --> 01:49:05,605
This is too terrible.

997
01:49:05,855 --> 01:49:07,565
Yes, it is.

998
01:49:09,317 --> 01:49:14,030
I know about Alan's reputation
as a philanderer. . .

999
01:49:14,697 --> 01:49:17,074
. . .but he'd never dream
of betraying me.

1000
01:49:19,827 --> 01:49:22,371
I gave him the Presidency.

1001
01:49:23,164 --> 01:49:24,790
Remember that press conference?

1002
01:49:25,041 --> 01:49:27,418
Where he put his arm
around you and said. . .

1003
01:49:27,668 --> 01:49:31,547
. . .if Christy hadn't been sick,
she'd have been in Barbados with you?

1004
01:49:31,756 --> 01:49:34,091
How the hell did he know
she was sick?

1005
01:49:34,926 --> 01:49:36,594
You didn't tell anyone.

1006
01:49:36,844 --> 01:49:39,055
It's because she told him that night.

1007
01:49:39,305 --> 01:49:41,390
I was right there watching.

1008
01:49:42,683 --> 01:49:44,685
That's not real proof.

1009
01:49:46,979 --> 01:49:48,606
Well, maybe this is, then.

1010
01:49:54,737 --> 01:49:56,322
You could've stolen this.

1011
01:49:57,782 --> 01:49:59,116
I did steal it.

1012
01:49:59,367 --> 01:50:02,828
But that's not my blood on there
and that's not my prints.

1013
01:50:30,481 --> 01:50:32,233
Mr. Sullivan.

1014
01:50:48,040 --> 01:50:50,626
I did love her, you know.

1015
01:51:11,439 --> 01:51:13,316
Jeez, Burton.

1016
01:51:59,904 --> 01:52:03,783
Is he working late? I don't have
an appointment but I want to see him.

1017
01:52:04,033 --> 01:52:06,285
You don't need an appointment.

1018
01:52:19,298 --> 01:52:20,633
Let's go, Miss Russell.

1019
01:53:03,301 --> 01:53:04,677
Walter.

1020
01:53:04,969 --> 01:53:05,803
Come in.

1021
01:53:10,141 --> 01:53:12,643
We interrupt with a breaking story...

1022
01:53:12,894 --> 01:53:15,146
... that's shocking
the nation and the world.

1023
01:53:15,396 --> 01:53:19,901
Information just came from the White
House about a tragedy within the hour.

1024
01:53:20,109 --> 01:53:22,028
We go now to our correspondent.

1025
01:53:22,278 --> 01:53:24,113
Diane, what can you tell us?

1026
01:53:26,115 --> 01:53:31,162
Sources tell us Walter Sullivan
had seen President Richmond tonight.

1027
01:53:31,370 --> 01:53:34,498
That was for an unscheduled
private meeting.

1028
01:53:44,967 --> 01:53:46,802
You're still here.

1029
01:53:49,805 --> 01:53:51,140
I'm still here.

1030
01:54:01,400 --> 01:54:03,486
--I would not be President.

1031
01:54:05,029 --> 01:54:08,074
If Christine had not taken ill. ..

1032
01:54:08,741 --> 01:54:11,410
...she would be with you
in Barbados even now.

1033
01:54:15,122 --> 01:54:17,917
Walter, you've been
like a father to me.

1034
01:54:18,167 --> 01:54:20,753
This is the President's
most recent news conference...

1035
01:54:20,962 --> 01:54:22,797
... where he clearly outlined...

1036
